main event: The observer reported seeing a dark-colored, funnel-shaped cloud-like object that did not make any noise over Springfield, Ohio on September 24, 1953.
interesting points: The object initially appeared as a 'jellyfish' projection and then took on a delta-wing configuration.
The object faded out and disappeared much like a star would.
The observer estimated the object to be slightly longer than 5 inches and have a metallic surface.
The object was observed for about 20 minutes and moved horizontally at a slow speed.
Another person, M/Sgt. [redacted], was with the observer and was also able to see the object.
